description: Presenting the Polo Ralph Lauren x Naiomi Glasses collection, the inaugural collaboration of the Ralph Lauren Artist in Residence programme, reflecting our evolved design approach with the artisans and communities that inspire us. The Polo Ralph Lauren x Naiomi Glasses collection honours Navajo heritage and centuries-old weaving traditions. Naiomi Glasses is a seventh-generation Diné (Navajo) textile artist and designer whose work reflects the beauty of her Indigenous culture. Through the first drop in this collection, Naiomi draws inspiration from her family, homelands and community on Dinétah (Navajo Nation). These unisex jeans are garment-dyed to achieve a relaxed look and tonal dimension.

description: Presenting the Polo Ralph Lauren x Naiomi Glasses collection, the inaugural collaboration of the Ralph Lauren Artist in Residence programme, reflecting our evolved design approach with the artisans and communities that inspire us. The Polo Ralph Lauren x Naiomi Glasses collection honours Navajo heritage and centuries-old weaving traditions. Naiomi Glasses is a seventh-generation Diné (Navajo) textile artist and designer whose work reflects the beauty of her Indigenous culture. Through the first drop in this collection, Naiomi draws inspiration from her family, homelands and community on Dinétah (Navajo Nation). These unisex indigo-dyed jeans are specially developed to perfectly emulate Naiomi's weavings with their embroidered Saltillo diamond, Spider Woman cross – a reference to the creator and protector of the weaving tradition in Navajo culture – and four-directional crosses. The four-directional cross and the number four carry great significance in Navajo tradition, as well as in other Native communities. They reference the Earth's four directions and the stars.

description: Presenting the Polo Ralph Lauren x Naiomi Glasses collection, the inaugural collaboration of the Ralph Lauren Artist in Residence programme, reflecting our evolved design approach with the artisans and communities that inspire us. The Polo Ralph Lauren x Naiomi Glasses collection honours Navajo heritage and centuries-old weaving traditions. Naiomi Glasses is a seventh-generation Diné (Navajo) textile artist and designer whose work reflects the beauty of her Indigenous culture. Through the first drop in this collection, Naiomi draws inspiration from her family, homelands and community on Dinétah (Navajo Nation). These unisex indigo-dyed jeans feature a custom-developed wash, which pays homage to the denim worn by her father and brother.
features_parsed: The fit of this unisex style is based on our standard men's sizing. We suggest that customers who usually order Polo Ralph Lauren women's clothing order two waist sizes larger than their usual size.

For example, if you usually order a women's size 27W, we suggest ordering a size 29W when purchasing this style. Male-presenting model is 185 cm and wears a size 32W x 32L. Female-presenting model is 178 cm and wears a size 30W x 32L.

The Heritage Rider: An authentic fit inspired by a vintage Western silhouette. Features a higher rise and is slim through the thigh. Kicks out at the leg opening to accommodate a boot. Size 32W has a 27.5 cm rise and a 45 cm leg opening.
Belt loops. Zip fly with a buttoned closure. Five-pocket styling with metal rivets. Exclusive "Polo" label with four-directional crosses on the coin pocket.
Exclusive leather "Polo Ralph Lauren & Co Naiomi Glasses" patch with four-directional crosses on the back right. Shell: 100% cotton. Decoration: 100% cow leather. Machine washable. Imported.

This product is sourced via a mass balance system and therefore may not contain Better Cotton™. Visit bettercotton.org/massbalance for more information about mass balance.

Five per cent of the purchase price from global sales of the first capsule of the Polo Ralph Lauren x Naiomi Glasses collection will benefit Change Labs – a Native-led organisation focused on fostering the creation of successful Navajo and Hopi small businesses.
*Excludes sales in the State of Mississippi and the State of Illinois.
